Massively pay-to-win. Event tourneys are cool in concept until you’re matched with someone who has put in either plenty of hours or plenty of money (probably the latter) and can have one player run through your entire squad because he’s 10 levels higher than you.  Drawing comparisons between yours and your opponent’s AI—even outside of tourneys—makes your players look like they react and think like a Sunday league compared to the brutally superior and simply unfair opponent AI despite no apparent level differences.  I’m not sure how you find better keepers, but I’ve noticed other players have different ones. If you get Taylor, I’d just delete the game as you’ll concede more than you’ll ever wish.  If you wanted a keeper worse than Kepa and David De Gea combined... well... that’s Taylor. However, the penalty system is well done though and I’ve found myself thoroughly enjoying when a game goes to pens even when I lose simply because of the intensity, and I’m pretty sure this is because there aren’t any stat advantages, so Mr. Maxed-Out-His-Credit has to play without his monetary advantage. 

I have many footy games on my phone, this by far has to be my least favorite one. Not a bad game per say, but there exists a myriad of better options from this one. Some AI fixes to raise player IQs higher than those of tadpoles and for them to actually follow their dotted paths and a true matchmaking feature could greatly improve this game. Until then, 3/5 for me. 

TLDR: AI is poor; matchmaking is nonexistent; penalty shootouts are quite redeemable.

I’ve been playing this game for over a year. It was very enjoyable. However, I made the mistake to actually put money into the game. The game isn’t worth putting any money into. The games are completely randomized. You never know what the CPU is going to do. As you rank up, you face different opponents but most of them have stronger players than you. So you’re stuck in this endless void of losing and not ranking up until you win just enough to be on the right level. The game is very buggy at times and the bs I’ve experienced have literally made me audibly laugh. I wouldn’t recommend this game just because of the sole glitches, bugs, and overall feel. I wish I could rate it higher but it’s just so many negatives compared to the positives.
